TI  - Digital Port Asset Management System (PAMS): A Predictive Framework for Data-Driven Maintenance in Port Infrastructure
PY  - 2025
T2  - Australasian Coasts and Ports 2025 Conference
SP  - 26
EP  - 29
UR  - https://www.scopus.com/pages/publications/105031747924?origin=resultslist
AB  - Ports are the essential infrastructures for world logistics with increasingly complex maintenance demands. Traditional asset management relies on scheduled inspections and reactive repairs, resulting in inefficiencies, high costs, and operational disruptions. This paper introduces the digital Port Asset Management System (PAMS), a machine learning-enabled framework designed to support predictive maintenance and long-term planning across various port assets. Though still in development, PAMS builds on digital twin technologies and integrates multi-source data, such as condition surveys, sensor feeds, and operational logs to forecast deterioration trends and optimise maintenance strategies. We present the conceptual framework and use cases for pavement and equipment maintenance, including an early-stage proof of concept for predictive crane modelling, emphasising the system's potential to reduce costs and improve reliability. While results are case dependent and will vary between locations, this paper highlights how predictive modelling and data integration will transform port maintenance strategies. © Australasian Coasts and Ports 2025.All rights reserved.
