AB  - In response to the increasing demand for greener and more efficient maritime solutions, Fincantieri has placed digital transformation and sustainability at the core of its strategic objectives. To support this mission, CETENA has developed an advanced onboard energy management system, called ASSIST ENERGY, that leverages digital twin technology to optimize ship operations and enhance decision-making. The system integrates seamlessly with ship automation frameworks to collect and analyze operational data, offering comprehensive insights into the vessel’s energy performance. Central to this solution is a sophisticated simulator that reproduces the ship’s energy behavior through agent-based modeling. This approach allows for detailed representation and interaction of individual components, enabling accurate predictions of system behavior under varying operational scenarios. A key innovation of the platform is its use of machine learning algorithms to identify optimal operational strategies, reduce energy consumption, and improve overall vessel efficiency. These algorithms dynamically adjust parameters based on real-time and historical data, enabling a continuous feedback loop for performance optimization. The collected data are accessible through user-friendly web platform available both onboard and onshore via cloud integration. This platform empowers ship operators and fleet managers with actionable insights, fostering data-driven decision-making processes. CETENA’s research efforts extend beyond shipboard operations through its participation in the MISSION project, aimed at integrating ship systems with port operations. By promoting just-in-time arrivals, this initiative minimizes port waiting times, optimizes speed profiles, and enhances navigational safety, contributing to the overall sustainability of maritime logistics. This paper discusses examples of simulation methodologies and optimization strategies in CETENA ASSIST ENERGY. Furthermore, it highlights the role of digital twins and machine learning in achieving sustainable maritime operations. © 2025 IOS Press.
