TI  - Smart Governance using an Integrated IoT Model in the Sultanate of Oman: Architecture and Pilots
PY  - 2026
T2  - ICIT 2025 - Proceedings of the 13th International Conference on Information Technology: IoT and Smart City
SP  - 38
EP  - 44
DO  - 10.1145/3787330.3787337
UR  - https://www.scopus.com/pages/publications/105035346572?origin=resultslist
AB  - The Sultanate of Oman has been at the forefront of digital transformation, sustainability, attainability of service excellence that are in alignment with Oman Vision 2040. However, there is a lot that needs to be achieved in order to be amongst the list of countries that have achieved the comprehensive transformation. It is essential in context to the Sultanate of Oman to build on national progress in logistic digitization, connectivity (5G, NB-IoT/LoRaWAN), smart metering besides other important areas. This research study proposes an Integrated Internet of Things (IoT) model tailored to Oman’s governance landscape. The model comprises six layers-Device, Connectivity, Edge, Context & Data, Intelligence, and Service & Governance. This model would be bound by cross-cutting controls for privacy, security, and interoperability. The model at its core is a NGSI-LD compliant context broker and a national sensor exchange enabling multi agency data sharing, digital twins, and real time decision support in Integrated Command & Control Centres (ICCCs). In this research study the architecture is translated into four Oman specific pilot domains: (1) Urban mobility & smart parking for Muscat corridors; (2) Water & energy telemetry integrating AMI smart meters with distribution operations; (3) Wadi flash flood and heat health early warning; and (4) Ports & logistics telematics across ASYAD’s ecosystem. The integrated model proposed in this research study demonstrates how the Sultanate of Oman can move from siloed verticals to vendor neutral and interoperable solutions that reduce time-to-value and protect data privacy. This research study is aligned with existing initiatives that the Sultanate of Oman is taking to position Oman to lead regionally in trustworthy and data-driven public services. © 2025 Copyright held by the owner/author(s).
